cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about improving the encoder-decoder model for natural language generation tasks, specifically in the headline generation task. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), which is typically classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses probability distributions and token-wise correspondence, which could relate to topics in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
